  "body": "NB! this issue needs to be researched and verified on very specific Android phones\n\n### User Story\n\nAs a user, I don't want to waste my precious batttery life for network\nconnections with Whisper peers if the node will be restarted anyway.\n\n### Description\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\n*Type*: Feature\n\nCurrently, when user minimizes the app on Android, Status Node doesn’t stop (it\nruns as a background service), so it keeps all connections to whisper peers\nalive. That keeps the phone to go to low-power mode.\n\n1. That actually wastes some battery on Android;\n\n1. Different “battery monitors” for Android complain about that.\n\n\nThe idea is to stop node (or at least pause it’s network activity) when the app\nis in background for a certain amount of time on Android.",
